By Sampson Unamka  Grammy-nominated artist Burna Boy via his instagram handle thanked Beniniose award winning singer, Angelique Kidjo, for dedicating the award to him. African Giant, as he fondly called, lost the Grammy for the category of Best World Music Album to Kidjo from her album: Celia.  Burna Boy, who went mute since the early hours of Monday, posted: “”I love you forever @angeliquekidjo and every single person that rooted for me, I don’t take any of it lightly! The world get ready cause we’re all coming! #FOOTONNECK2020.” Kidjo has won over 100 awards, including four Grammys.